      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. but i'm trying to avoid just making a generic \"city\" collection. when people label something as \"urban\" streetwear, they're usually thinking of very specific groups or demographics, right? like, if i want to capture that specific look, should i be focusing on certain ethnic or racial aesthetics to make it feel \"authentic\" rather than just looking like random baggy clothes?",
